cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use the Agentic SDLC Incident Taxonomy (ASIT), please cite it as below."
title: "Agentic SDLC Incident Taxonomy (ASIT)"
abstract: >-
  A public, citable taxonomy of failure modes in which an autonomous or
  semi-autonomous coding agent is the proximate cause of a software development
  lifecycle defect, breach, outage, or governance failure. Each category is
  testable, cross-referenced to a governance control map, and tagged as
  documented (backed by a sourced public incident) or anticipated.
type: dataset
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-24"
license: MIT
